ğŸ§° Installation
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-project-name.git
cd your-project-name

2. Create a virtual environment (recommended)
python -m venv venv


Activate it:

Windows

venv\Scripts\activate


Linux/macOS

source venv/bin/activate

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run the CLI
python main.py

ğŸ§ª Usage

Start the CLI and follow the interactive menu.

Sending a Request

Choose an HTTP method

Enter the URL

Add any headers

Add a JSON body (optional)

View full response details:
status, headers, timing, and body

Saved Requests

Store frequently-used API calls in a JSON file.
Re-run them instantly.

View History

Every request you send is automatically logged.

